org.ensor.data.atom

Class Atom

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.ensor.data.atom.Atom
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    BoolAtom, DictionaryAtom, ImmutableDict, ImmutableList, IntAtom, ListAtom, RealAtom, StringAtom

    public abstract class Atom
extends Object
    An atom is the primitive abstract data container for events. It consists of a type and derived classes hold the actual data associated with the atom.
    Author:
    Jon

      • getImmutable

        public abstract Atom getImmutable()
        This method can be used to obtain an immutable representation of the same data structure. Most of the primitive types are already immutable and only the container (list, dictionary) types undergo some type of conversion in order to provide an immutable version.
        Returns:
        An immutable version of the atom.
